				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/radiodog" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1241703); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1241703&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163877" alt="Radiodog" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1241703)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/radiodog" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1241703); return false;" >Radiodog</a></span> <span class="odate time_1324122081 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Dec 2011 11:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1329972">
									

<p>While I enjoy the tone and style, I can't say I'm too fond of the message. This is the organization that has restructured reality several times. That has contained reality benders and made people accept the concept of colour (SCP-8900-EX). I can't see a few cities being damaged by the eternal antagonist causing them to change their mandate.</p>
<p>The Foundation is more than just a bureaucracy who changes their motive based on public opinion/knowledge. It is not in the business of forgiveness or mercy, for these concepts have no bearing on containment for the sake of the maintaining peace in a war against a hostile universe. It is an extension of human fear, doubt and blind hope made manifest.</p>

							</div>

								
					
